    "This may be related to section 230 of the Communications Decency Act of 1996, which provides immunity to online platforms, including search engines, for content produced by third parties.",
    "In contrast, a genAI company is considered a content creator and would be liable if its material caused harm.",
    "However, despite the potential risk, from a public health perspective, the guardrails on genAI tools may be too restrictive.",
    "The tools accurately identified our queries as being sensitive in nature, but preventing the return of any potentially controversial or harmful content seems to have been prioritized above offering support or evidence-based content.",
    "It may be that the public failures of early attempts to use genAI tools for mental health purposes [46, 47, 70] had a chilling effect on the field."
